<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 27 at 8:35PM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A SHOWER WILL AFFECT
PITTSYLVANIA COUNTY AND THE CITY OF DANVILLE...
At 833 PM EST, a band of heavy rain was located over Dry Fork, or
near Blairs, moving northeast at 35 mph. This band was producing
rainfall at rates of 1 to 2 inches per hour.
Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Altavista...
Hurt...
Chatham...
Gretna...
Blairs...
and Mt Airy.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
